    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>This addition to the papers of the 
         <persname>American Rhododendron Society</persname>, containing
         ca. 1,000 items (4 Hollinger boxes, ca. 1 linear foot),
         1949-1989, consists of general correspondence, financial
         papers and bound volumes, minutes of the Board of Directors,
         chapter information forms, "The Fundamentals of Rhododendron
         and Azalea Culture" by 
         <persname>J. Harold Clarke</persname>(printed), notes and
         chronologies for an 
         <persname>American Rhododendron Society</persname>history,
         policies of the Board of Directors, and a compilation of
         rhododendron varieties suitable for different areas of the 
         <geogname>United States</geogname>by the 
         <corpname>Van Veen Nursery</corpname>.</p>
      <p>There are also correspondence files for several committees
         and topics of interest to the membership. Among these are: the
         <corpname>Bylaws Implementation Committee</corpname>, the 
         <corpname>Honors Committee</corpname>, the 
         <corpname>International Rhododendron Union</corpname>, the 
         <corpname>Long Range Planning Committee</corpname>, the 
         <corpname>National Convention Committee</corpname>, the 
         <corpname>Nominating Committee</corpname>, the 
         <corpname>Committee for Planning for a National Headquarters
         and the Proposal to Purchase the Cecil Smith
         property</corpname>, Plant Registrar, Pollen Bank and Seed
         Exchange, the 
         <corpname>Public Relations Committee</corpname>, the 
         <corpname>Ratings Committee</corpname>, and the 
         <corpname>Research Committee</corpname>.</p>
      <p>The general correspondence files chiefly contain
         correspondence with chapters and their presidents, the
         executive secretaries, the editor of the 
         <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Quarterly Bulletin</title></bibref>, and other officers of the organization.</p>
      <p>Several issues that reoccurred frequently in this
         correspondence include the filling of the office of Executive
         Secretary (1976 Feb 28, Mar 30, Apr 1, 12, 19, &amp; 29, May
         17, and Jun 1); the publication of 
         <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Rhododendrons of China</title></bibref>(1979 Jun 26, &amp; Dec 12; 1980 Feb 13, Oct 22, 23;
         1981 Nov 5); the concern over the dues increase (1983 Nov
         11-1984 Sep 4; and 1985 Mar 6-Apr 12); the 
         <corpname>Japanese Rhododendron Society</corpname>(1984 Aug 12
         &amp; 17); the Executive Director Search Committee and the
         Executive Secretary (1989 Feb 11-Mar 15, n.d.); and the
         Endowment Fund (1984 Nov 12, 1985 Mar 30, 1988 Feb 20, and Mar
         2 &amp; 15).</p>
      <p>The collection is arranged chronologically by topic, name
         of committee, or type of material.</p>
    </scopecontent>
